HEADWORD: Spurry
<hw>Spur"ry</hw> <pr>(sp⟦ucr⟧r"r⟦ycr⟧)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[D. or
OF. <ets>spurrie</ets>; cf. G. <ets>spergel</ets>, NL.
<ets>spergula</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>An annual herb
(<spn>Spergula arvensis</spn>) with whorled filiform leaves, sometimes
grown in Europe for fodder.</def> <altsp>[Written also
<asp>spurrey</asp>.]</altsp>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Sand spurry</b></col> <fld>(Bot.)</fld>, <cd>any low herb
of the genus <gen>Lepigonum</gen>, mostly found in sandy
places.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Spur-shell</ent>⟦br⟧
